NODE_1_length_340355_cov_492.662176	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	202321	205176	.	+	0	ID=MGA_173;product=FtsX-like permease family protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_013390053.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_01720;note=WP_013390053.1 FtsX-like permease family protein (Bifidobacterium bifidum) [pid:56.3%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:100.0%25%2C Eval:5.8e-281],COG:COG0577:SalY ABC-type antimicrobial peptide transport system%2C permease component [Category:V%2C Aligned:218-452%2C Eval:7.1e-16%2C score:77.8%2C N-term missing],Domain:cl27391:FtsX FtsX-like permease family. Members of this protein family are found%2C so far%2C only in three species of Acidobacteria%2C namely Acidobacteria bacterium Ellin345%2C Acidobacterium capsulatum ATCC 51196%2C and Solibacter usitatus Ellin6076%2C where they form large paralogous families. Each protein contains two copies of a domain called the efflux ABC transporter permease protein (pfam02687). However%2C unlike other members of that family (including LolC%2C FtsX%2C and MacB)%2C genes for these proteins are essentially never found fused or adjacent to ABC transporter ATP-binding protein (pfam00005) genes. We name this family ADOP%2C for Acidobacterial Duplicated Orphan Permease%2C to reflect the restricted lineage%2C internal duplication%2C lack of associated ATP-binding cassette proteins%2C and permease homology. The function is unknown. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:816-869%2C Eval:1.4e-07%2C score:51.9%2C C-term missing],MGA_173
