NODE_3_length_166080_cov_616.906592	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	131929	132804	.	-	0	ID=MGA_640;product=D-hexose-6-phosphate mutarotase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011068503.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_06380;note=WP_011068503.1 D-hexose-6-phosphate mutarotase (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:98.3%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:95.4%25%2C Eval:2.7e-170],Domain:cl14648:Aldose_epim aldose 1-epimerase superfamily. Members of this protein family act as galactose mutarotase (D-galactose 1-epimerase) and participate in the Leloir pathway for galactose/glucose interconversion. All members of the seed alignment for this model are found in gene clusters with other enzymes of the Leloir pathway. This enzyme family belongs to the aldose 1-epimerase family%2C described by pfam01263. However%2C the enzyme described as aldose 1-epimerase itself (EC 5.1.3.3) is called broadly specific for D-glucose%2C L-arabinose%2C D-xylose%2C D-galactose%2C maltose and lactose. The restricted genome context for genes in this family suggests members should act primarily on D-galactose. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:10-290%2C Eval:8.4e-57%2C score:181.8],MGA_640
