NODE_20_length_35025_cov_399.336157	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	3508	4140	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1532;product=phospholipase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_052787970.1;translation=MQMTSQIDAGGNDPIFLMFHGYGNDESEMMRILDAVYAPTRADAAPAAIAAVPSYISFRATYARPYMGGNYWYPDGCGVDERQRECAAVGDAVASLLDASAFAHRRKILIGFSQGGYLSYRLVKVHPTLFDAAILLSPSFMGEEQAALDSPTRFFLAYGAQDRTIPLPDQQTAHQVLERAGHLTYREYSGMAHAICDEEIADIRDFLRAI;locus_tag=LOCUS_15180;note=WP_052787970.1 phospholipase (Bifidobacterium breve) [pid:73.1%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:94.7%25%2C Eval:2.9e-92],Domain:cl21494:Abhydrolase alpha/beta hydrolases. This family consists of several chlorophyllase and chlorophyllase-2 (EC:3.1.1.14) enzymes. Chlorophyllase (Chlase) is the first enzyme involved in chlorophyll (Chl) degradation and catalyzes the hydrolysis of an ester bond to yield chlorophyllide and phytol. The family includes both plant and Amphioxus members. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:12-207%2C Eval:1.7e-26%2C score:98.1],MGA_1532
