NODE_25_length_29958_cov_619.336435	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	15383	16492	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1678;product=tRNA glutamyl-Q(34) synthetase GluQRS;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_007053096.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_16610;note=WP_007053096.1 tRNA glutamyl-Q(34) synthetase GluQRS (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:97.3%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:97.4%25%2C Eval:2.5e-214],Domain:cl27212:GlnS Glutamyl- or glutaminyl-tRNA synthetase [Translation%2C ribosomal structure and biogenesis]. The glutamyl-tRNA synthetases of the eukaryotic cytosol and of the Archaea are more similar to glutaminyl-tRNA synthetases than to bacterial glutamyl-tRNA synthetases. This model models just the bacterial and mitochondrial forms of the enzyme. In many species%2C the charging of tRNA(gln) proceeds first through misacylation with Glu and then transamidation. For this reason%2C glutamyl-tRNA synthetases may act on both tRNA(gln) and tRNA(glu). This model is highly specific. Proteins with positive scores below the trusted cutoff may be fragments rather than full-length sequences. [Protein synthesis%2C tRNA aminoacylation] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-327%2C Eval:7.6e-75%2C score:236.8%2C C-term missing],MGA_1678
